lead_paragraph: Egyptians marked the fifth anniversary of the uprising that toppled President Hosni Mubarak with a handful of flash protests but none of the violence or anger that drove the uprising.
snippet: Egyptians marked the fifth anniversary of the uprising that toppled President Hosni Mubarak with a handful of flash protests but none of the violence or anger that drove the uprising.

headline.main: Police Presence in Egypt Mutes Most Protests on 5th Anniversary of Uprising
headline.print_headline: Police Presence in Egypt Mutes Most Protests on 5th Anniversary of Uprising

abstract: Handful of antigovernment demonstrations in Cairo, on anniversary of 2011 ouster of Egyptian Pres Hosni Mubarak,are easily quelled by authorities; recent crackdown on political opposition by regime of Pres Abdel Fattah el-Sisi has left few activists free to protest; some residents express gratitude for relative stability.
